==English==
===Etymology===
French [[péricarpe]], from Latin [[pericarpium]], from Greek [[περικαρπιον]] ‘pod, husk, shell’, from [[περι-]] + [[καρπος]] ‘fruit’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'pɛrɪkɑ:p/

===Noun===
{{en-noun|pericarp|pericarps}}
#{{botany}}: The outermost layer of a ripe [[fruit]] or [[ovary]].

